article_title: Insurance enrollment up after Obamacare website fixes

article_metadata.description: After two months of letdowns, the federal government’s health-insurance website appears to be back from the brink — and not a moment too soon. Yesterday was the original deadline for Ohioans to enroll in a plan through the federal HealthCare.gov website if they wanted their coverage to begin Jan. 1, when health insurance becomes mandatory for most Americans. But given the magnitude of the technical problems with the website, the government pushed that deadline back to Dec. 23, giving people eight additional days to enroll.
